777
00:28:07,830 --> 00:28:09,090
that you're focusing on many things

778
00:28:09,090 --> 00:28:11,913
or that arrow shifts to a
different location in the room.

779
00:28:11,913 --> 00:28:14,220
The key is to be able to shift it back

780
00:28:14,220 --> 00:28:16,927
and to narrow it once again
and that's an active process,

781
00:28:16,927 --> 00:28:20,340
so much so that it requires
a lot of metabolic energy,

782
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:25,113
your brain is the chief
consumer of metabolic energy.

783
00:28:25,113 --> 00:28:26,607
The calories that you consume,

784
00:28:26,607 --> 00:28:28,170
the so-called basal metabolic rate,

785
00:28:28,170 --> 00:28:29,250
most of that isn't related

786
00:28:29,250 --> 00:28:30,690
to movement or heartbeat or breathing,

787
00:28:30,690 --> 00:28:32,520
it's related to brain function.

788
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:35,880
Your brain is a glutton with
respect to caloric need.

789
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,800
So understand that at
the end of 90 minutes

790
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:39,390
or maybe even after 45 minutes,

791
00:28:39,390 --> 00:28:42,090
you might feel rather
tired or even exhausted.

792
00:28:42,090 --> 00:28:45,150
And it's very important
that after a about of focus

793
00:28:45,150 --> 00:28:46,890
that you take at least 10 minutes

794
00:28:46,890 --> 00:28:48,960
and ideally as long as 30 minutes

795
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:51,600
and go through what I
call deliberate defocus.

796
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:54,210
You really want to focus
on somewhat menial tasks

797
00:28:54,210 --> 00:28:55,800
or things that really don't require

