1913
01:10:13,320 --> 01:10:17,520
I might do another NSDR
of 10 to 30 or 60 minutes,

1914
01:10:17,520 --> 01:10:18,840
and then another work about.

1915
01:10:18,840 --> 01:10:21,420
Again, NSDR is something I do every day.

1916
01:10:21,420 --> 01:10:24,240
I talked a lot about this in
the episodes related to sleep,

1917
01:10:24,240 --> 01:10:25,560
because it can help you get better

1918
01:10:25,560 --> 01:10:28,020
at falling and staying asleep at night

1919
01:10:28,020 --> 01:10:30,990
in addition to feeling restorative

1920
01:10:30,990 --> 01:10:32,700
in that immediate timeframe of the day

1921
01:10:32,700 --> 01:10:33,960
in which you do NSDR,

1922
01:10:33,960 --> 01:10:35,970
so it's immensely
beneficial at various times

1923
01:10:35,970 --> 01:10:37,530
and for various purposes.

1924
01:10:37,530 --> 01:10:39,060
But here within the context

1925
01:10:39,060 --> 01:10:40,530
of trying to concentrate and focus

1926
01:10:40,530 --> 01:10:42,300
when you're sleep deprived,

1927
01:10:42,300 --> 01:10:46,920
NSDR, AKA yoga nidra is an
immensely beneficial practice.

1928
01:10:46,920 --> 01:10:49,410
There's growing amounts of quality science

1929
01:10:49,410 --> 01:10:52,770
pointing to the neurochemical
replenishing effects,

1930
01:10:52,770 --> 01:10:54,450
as I mentioned before, dopamine,

