1934
01:11:01,220 --> 01:11:03,120
as a total replacement for sleep,

1935
01:11:03,120 --> 01:11:05,910
but under conditions in which
you cannot control your sleep,

1936
01:11:05,910 --> 01:11:08,640
NSDR is going to be the
best way that I am aware of

1937
01:11:08,640 --> 01:11:11,670
to restore your ability
to focus and concentrate

1938
01:11:11,670 --> 01:11:13,080
for whatever purpose.

1939
01:11:13,080 --> 01:11:14,850
And if you emerge from your NSDR

1940
01:11:14,850 --> 01:11:15,930
and then drink some caffeine,

1941
01:11:15,930 --> 01:11:18,340
you'll notice an even greater capacity

1942
01:11:18,340 --> 01:11:20,190
for focus and concentration

1943
01:11:20,190 --> 01:11:22,710
for all the reasons directly
related to caffeine.

1944
01:11:22,710 --> 01:11:25,710
So again, NSDR is a general tool

1945
01:11:25,710 --> 01:11:27,827
for enhancing your ability to sleep

1946
01:11:27,827 --> 01:11:29,760
and it's a tool that you can use

1947
01:11:29,760 --> 01:11:32,880
in order to compensate for,
at least to some degree,

1948
01:11:32,880 --> 01:11:34,740
compensate for lost sleep

1949
01:11:34,740 --> 01:11:36,660
when you need to focus and concentrate.

1950
01:11:36,660 --> 01:11:39,840
