2092
01:16:46,530 --> 01:16:48,480
Now there's another
set of behavioral tools

2093
01:16:48,480 --> 01:16:51,420
that can really help enhance
one's ability to focus

2094
01:16:51,420 --> 01:16:53,614
and those are visual based tools.

2095
01:16:53,614 --> 01:16:55,830
In fact, the tools I'm about to describe

2096
01:16:55,830 --> 01:16:58,770
are actually being employed
in a number of schools

2097
01:16:58,770 --> 01:17:01,680
in China and elsewhere in
order to teach children

2098
01:17:01,680 --> 01:17:04,743
to focus better and for
longer periods of time.

2099
01:17:05,670 --> 01:17:10,590
The key principle here is that
much of our cognitive focus,

2100
01:17:10,590 --> 01:17:13,110
our ability to think about
something in a very specific way

2101
01:17:13,110 --> 01:17:14,550
and stay focused on it,

2102
01:17:14,550 --> 01:17:18,090
to read or to follow
a line of conversation

2103
01:17:18,090 --> 01:17:20,250
or math or music, et cetera,

2104
01:17:20,250 --> 01:17:24,030
is going to be directed
by our visual system.

2105
01:17:24,030 --> 01:17:26,520
Our visual system has two
forms of attention and focus.

2106
01:17:26,520 --> 01:17:29,430
One is overt focus, which
is very straightforward.

2107
01:17:29,430 --> 01:17:30,780
If I'm looking at the tip of my pen,

2108
01:17:30,780 --> 01:17:31,800
for those of who are listening right now,

2109
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:33,840
I'm looking at the tip of
my pen, that's overt focus,

2110
01:17:33,840 --> 01:17:35,610
I'm focusing on it with my eyes,

2111
01:17:35,610 --> 01:17:38,220
and of course, the rest of
my brain then will follow

2112
01:17:38,220 --> 01:17:40,377
and start to analyze the
details of what I'm seeing

2113
01:17:40,377 --> 01:17:42,630
and the contours of the pen, et cetera.

2114
01:17:42,630 --> 01:17:44,670
It seems sort of obvious
when you first hear it,

2115
01:17:44,670 --> 01:17:47,220
but our cognitive focus tends to follow

2116
01:17:47,220 --> 01:17:49,530
our overt visual focus.

2117
01:17:49,530 --> 01:17:51,780
That's also why they
put blinders on horses.

2118
01:17:51,780 --> 01:17:54,960
That's also why sometimes
wearing a hoodie or a hat

2119
01:17:54,960 --> 01:17:57,301
or limiting your visual field in some way

2120
01:17:57,301 --> 01:18:00,140
can help you enhance your cognitive focus,

2121
01:18:00,140 --> 01:18:01,650
it can help limit distraction.

2122
01:18:01,650 --> 01:18:03,870
You're just not seeing as much.

2123
01:18:03,870 --> 01:18:05,700
It's also why when we ingest caffeine

2124
01:18:05,700 --> 01:18:07,590
or any kind of stimulant
or we are stressed

2125
01:18:07,590 --> 01:18:08,910
and our pupils dilate

2126
01:18:08,910 --> 01:18:10,560
and our vision becomes more tunnel-like,

2127
01:18:10,560 --> 01:18:12,420
less panoramic, but more tunnel-like,

2128
01:18:12,420 --> 01:18:14,220
you know they say a soda
straw view of the world

2129
01:18:14,220 --> 01:18:15,794
or you're looking through a tunnel,

2130
01:18:15,794 --> 01:18:18,150
your focus, your visual focus

2131
01:18:18,150 --> 01:18:19,920
is actually driving your cognitive focus.

2132
01:18:19,920 --> 01:18:23,100
Your cognitive focus is
narrower than it would be

2133
01:18:23,100 --> 01:18:24,960
if you were seeing the
whole scene that you're in.

2134
01:18:24,960 --> 01:18:26,400
So when you hear this, it sounds obvious,

2135
01:18:26,400 --> 01:18:28,620
but for many people,
including many scientists,

2136
01:18:28,620 --> 01:18:30,420
it's just not obvious that
this would be the case.

2137
01:18:30,420 --> 01:18:31,890
However, that is the case,

2138
01:18:31,890 --> 01:18:34,800
your visual focus drives
your cognitive focus.

2139
01:18:34,800 --> 01:18:36,480
So what is a practice

2140
01:18:36,480 --> 01:18:39,570
that has been studied
in various laboratories

2141
01:18:39,570 --> 01:18:41,190
and that's being employed
in various schools?

2142
01:18:41,190 --> 01:18:46,190
Is to have children or adults
visually focus on one location

2143
01:18:46,980 --> 01:18:48,570
for a given period of time.

2144
01:18:48,570 --> 01:18:49,560
How long?

2145
01:18:49,560 --> 01:18:52,290
Anywhere from 30 seconds to three minutes,

2146
01:18:52,290 --> 01:18:53,123
and believe it or not,

2147
01:18:53,123 --> 01:18:53,956
three minutes is a long time

2148
01:18:53,956 --> 01:18:56,666
to maintain visual focus at one location.

2149
01:18:56,666 --> 01:18:58,140
If you were to try that right now,

2150
01:18:58,140 --> 01:19:00,150
you'd probably find it
to be a bit of a strain,

2151
01:19:00,150 --> 01:19:01,800
but if you want to try it, you can.

2152
01:19:01,800 --> 01:19:05,100
Keep in mind, you yes,
are allowed to blink,

2153
01:19:05,100 --> 01:19:08,700
but also keep in mind that
meditation refocusing practice

2154
01:19:08,700 --> 01:19:10,290
that we talked about earlier,

2155
01:19:10,290 --> 01:19:13,560
that the refocusing is the key component

2156
01:19:13,560 --> 01:19:15,841
of teaching yourself or your brain,

2157
01:19:15,841 --> 01:19:17,430
you are your brain, your brain is you,

2158
01:19:17,430 --> 01:19:19,860
but to teach yourself how to focus better.

2159
01:19:19,860 --> 01:19:23,190
So if you're going to
incorporate this practice,

2160
01:19:23,190 --> 01:19:25,350
what you would want to
do is pick a location,

2161
01:19:25,350 --> 01:19:26,460
it could be on a wall,

2162
01:19:26,460 --> 01:19:28,230
it could be on your
computer in front of you,

2163
01:19:28,230 --> 01:19:29,130
although I would encourage it

2164
01:19:29,130 --> 01:19:31,020
to not be the contents
of your computer screen,

2165
01:19:31,020 --> 01:19:32,670
you might just want to blank your screen,

2166
01:19:32,670 --> 01:19:33,870
you might want to put a piece of paper

2167
01:19:33,870 --> 01:19:36,660
with a crosshatch there,
any sort of visual target,

2168
01:19:36,660 --> 01:19:38,100
or you can imagine a visual target

2169
01:19:38,100 --> 01:19:40,500
and then focus your visual
attention on that target

2170
01:19:40,500 --> 01:19:43,020
and try to breathe normally,
try and stay relaxed,

2171
01:19:43,020 --> 01:19:44,430
and certainly allow yourself to blink

2172
01:19:44,430 --> 01:19:45,870
so that your eyes don't try out.

2173
01:19:45,870 --> 01:19:49,230
This is not a test of how long
you can go without blinking.

2174
01:19:49,230 --> 01:19:51,900
By focusing on that particular location

2175
01:19:51,900 --> 01:19:54,450
and by forcing yourself to
refocus on that location

2176
01:19:54,450 --> 01:19:58,770
anytime your gaze, your vision
drifts from that location,

2177
01:19:58,770 --> 01:20:02,130
you are encouraging the circuits for focus

2178
01:20:02,130 --> 01:20:04,350
to get better at focusing
for longer and longer

2179
01:20:04,350 --> 01:20:06,210
and at refocusing when your focus

2180
01:20:06,210 --> 01:20:08,040
drifts off of that location.

2181
01:20:08,040 --> 01:20:09,600
This is incorporating neural circuits,

2182
01:20:09,600 --> 01:20:11,040
including the prefrontal cortex,

2183
01:20:11,040 --> 01:20:12,570
things like the frontal eye fields.

2184
01:20:12,570 --> 01:20:14,748
For those of you curious
about the underlying biology,

2185
01:20:14,748 --> 01:20:18,000
this practice is
recruiting certain elements

2186
01:20:18,000 --> 01:20:19,500
of your so-called prefrontal cortex,

2187
01:20:19,500 --> 01:20:21,480
also the frontal eye fields,

2188
01:20:21,480 --> 01:20:24,150
which are locations not far
from the prefrontal cortex,

2189
01:20:24,150 --> 01:20:26,640
that are involved in
deliberately directing your gaze

2190
01:20:26,640 --> 01:20:29,190
to particular locations in space,

2191
01:20:29,190 --> 01:20:30,090
not outer space,

2192
01:20:30,090 --> 01:20:32,820
although you could do this by
focusing on stars I suppose,

2193
01:20:32,820 --> 01:20:35,100
but in visual space.

2194
01:20:35,100 --> 01:20:36,480
Now I mentioned before

2195
01:20:36,480 --> 01:20:39,870
that this is overt visual
focus and attention,

2196
01:20:39,870 --> 01:20:42,030
you are overtly looking at that location,

2197
01:20:42,030 --> 01:20:44,400
but one also very powerful practice

2198
01:20:44,400 --> 01:20:48,060
for improving focus and concentration

2199
01:20:48,060 --> 01:20:50,610
is to use covert focus.

2200
01:20:50,610 --> 01:20:53,190
Covert focus is where my gaze,

2201
01:20:53,190 --> 01:20:56,310
my eyes are focused on one
location, such as my pen,

2202
01:20:56,310 --> 01:20:58,770
but my focus is actually directed

2203
01:20:58,770 --> 01:21:01,500
elsewhere in the room
or location that I'm in.

2204
01:21:01,500 --> 01:21:05,580
My mind and to some extent
my peripheral vision

2205
01:21:05,580 --> 01:21:08,130
is focused in this case on
the door just to my left

2206
01:21:08,130 --> 01:21:09,360
in the room that I'm in.

2207
01:21:09,360 --> 01:21:10,740
That takes a little bit more effort.

2208
01:21:10,740 --> 01:21:12,750
This is something that
all old world primates,

2209
01:21:12,750 --> 01:21:15,630
of which we are old world
primates, are able to do.

2210
01:21:15,630 --> 01:21:18,030
And it probably evolved
as part of the mechanism

2211
01:21:18,030 --> 01:21:21,870
by which animals could
evaluate their scene,

2212
01:21:21,870 --> 01:21:25,800
evaluate predators,
evaluate other primates

2213
01:21:25,800 --> 01:21:28,620
while not necessarily
staring at them directly

2214
01:21:28,620 --> 01:21:30,330
so they can obtain information,

2215
01:21:30,330 --> 01:21:32,880
we can obtain information
without having to direct our gaze

2216
01:21:32,880 --> 01:21:34,230
specifically to one location.

2217
01:21:34,230 --> 01:21:37,140
Maybe we can obtain information
from multiple locations,

2218
01:21:37,140 --> 01:21:38,790
indeed, we can.

2219
01:21:38,790 --> 01:21:41,460
Without getting too far
down the rabbit hole

2220
01:21:41,460 --> 01:21:44,640
of how vision and cognition relate,

2221
01:21:44,640 --> 01:21:46,897
because we've done episodes
on that previously,

2222
01:21:46,897 --> 01:21:51,720
and simply focusing on the
tools that can be incorporated

2223
01:21:51,720 --> 01:21:55,140
to improve focus and concentration,
here's what I recommend.

2224
01:21:55,140 --> 01:22:00,060
Set yourself a low bar
at first and set a timer

2225
01:22:00,060 --> 01:22:03,570
and try to focus on one
location for 30 seconds

2226
01:22:03,570 --> 01:22:05,130
and that's it for that day.

2227
01:22:05,130 --> 01:22:07,170
The next day, you might add five seconds,

2228
01:22:07,170 --> 01:22:09,300
and then the next day,
five seconds after that.

2229
01:22:09,300 --> 01:22:11,190
If you miss a day, no big deal,

2230
01:22:11,190 --> 01:22:14,520
simply do the practice for
the same amount of time

2231
01:22:14,520 --> 01:22:16,680
that you did the last time
that you did the practice,

2232
01:22:16,680 --> 01:22:19,800
and then gradually try and
increase the amount of time

2233
01:22:19,800 --> 01:22:23,100
that you can focus on one
visual location overtly

2234
01:22:23,100 --> 01:22:25,261
by looking directly at that location.

2235
01:22:25,261 --> 01:22:28,020
If you like, and if you
feel you have the ability,

2236
01:22:28,020 --> 01:22:30,870
you can try and do this through
covert attention and focus

2237
01:22:30,870 --> 01:22:32,760
by looking straight forward for instance,

2238
01:22:32,760 --> 01:22:34,560
and attending to something
in the corner of the room

2239
01:22:34,560 --> 01:22:36,780
and trying to do that for 30 seconds,

2240
01:22:36,780 --> 01:22:38,460
you'll find that that's
quite a bit harder,

2241
01:22:38,460 --> 01:22:40,560
and then extending that by five seconds

2242
01:22:40,560 --> 01:22:42,360
every time you do the practice.

2243
01:22:42,360 --> 01:22:44,280
This is something that I
don't think you necessarily

2244
01:22:44,280 --> 01:22:46,350
have to build up to being
able to do for a full hour

2245
01:22:46,350 --> 01:22:47,760
in order to extract the benefits.

2246
01:22:47,760 --> 01:22:50,520
In fact, the best way to
think about this practice

2247
01:22:50,520 --> 01:22:53,400
is as a means to get into a focused state.

2248
01:22:53,400 --> 01:22:56,640
If you remember back
about an hour or so ago,

2249
01:22:56,640 --> 01:22:59,040
I was talking about how focused states

2250
01:22:59,040 --> 01:23:03,510
are not a drop all the way in
and then exit type phenomenon.

2251
01:23:03,510 --> 01:23:05,190
We don't just drop into a focused state

2252
01:23:05,190 --> 01:23:07,170
the same way we don't drop
into the peak performance

2253
01:23:07,170 --> 01:23:08,850
of a workout, we warm up.

2254
01:23:08,850 --> 01:23:12,450
So what I recommend is having a 30 second

2255
01:23:12,450 --> 01:23:17,450
to three minute period at the
beginning of a about to focus

2256
01:23:17,580 --> 01:23:19,590
where you're going to
do work or physical work

2257
01:23:19,590 --> 01:23:23,490
and anchoring your vision to one location

2258
01:23:23,490 --> 01:23:24,810
somewhere in the room

2259
01:23:24,810 --> 01:23:26,850
or if you want to do it
covertly, you can do that,

2260
01:23:26,850 --> 01:23:28,500
setting a timer and trying to do that

2261
01:23:28,500 --> 01:23:30,720
for anywhere from 30
seconds to three minutes.

2262
01:23:30,720 --> 01:23:34,980
What you're doing when
you exercise that practice

2263
01:23:34,980 --> 01:23:38,160
is you are ramping up neural activity

2264
01:23:38,160 --> 01:23:39,690
within the neural circuits

2265
01:23:39,690 --> 01:23:41,910
that create focus and concentration.

2266
01:23:41,910 --> 01:23:44,520
Then, I would stop
looking at that location

2267
01:23:44,520 --> 01:23:45,720
or that covert location

2268
01:23:45,720 --> 01:23:47,520
and then I would move to the
work that you're trying to do,

2269
01:23:47,520 --> 01:23:49,710
either mental work or physical work.

2270
01:23:49,710 --> 01:23:52,470
And if about halfway
through your 90 minute about

2271
01:23:52,470 --> 01:23:55,200
or at some point in your 90
minute about of work or exercise,

2272
01:23:55,200 --> 01:23:57,090
you feel that your
concentration is drifting

2273
01:23:57,090 --> 01:23:58,380
rather than look at your phone

2274
01:23:58,380 --> 01:24:01,080
and scroll through the
thousands of contexts

2275
01:24:01,080 --> 01:24:03,390
that exists within social
media or your phone,

2276
01:24:03,390 --> 01:24:05,790
try just picking a
