01:34:03,720 --> 01:34:06,810
Again, L-tyrosine can be
derived from food sources,

2526
01:34:06,810 --> 01:34:07,710
I invite you to look up

2527
01:34:07,710 --> 01:34:09,090
those various food sources on the web,

2528
01:34:09,090 --> 01:34:10,770
simply go to a web browser and put in

2529
01:34:10,770 --> 01:34:12,420
foods that contain a lot of L-tyrosine

2530
01:34:12,420 --> 01:34:14,996
and you'll get a rich array
of choices to select from.

2531
01:34:14,996 --> 01:34:19,470
But in my case, I use
L-tyrosine in capsule form.

2532
01:34:19,470 --> 01:34:21,734
I will take 500 milligrams of L-tyrosine,

2533
01:34:21,734 --> 01:34:25,170
300 milligrams of Alpha-GPC
and a cup of coffee.

2534
01:34:25,170 --> 01:34:27,210
I'm careful to do this early in the day,

2535
01:34:27,210 --> 01:34:28,920
certainly not after two or 3:00 PM

2536
01:34:28,920 --> 01:34:31,020
because I don't want
to diminish my ability

2537
01:34:31,020 --> 01:34:32,626
to fall and stay asleep that night.

2538
01:34:32,626 --> 01:34:34,740
I'll do this early in
the day before a workout

2539
01:34:34,740 --> 01:34:38,444
or before a about of
concentrated mental work.

2540
01:34:38,444 --> 01:34:41,730
Again, I tend to do this
about four days per week,

2541
01:34:41,730 --> 01:34:45,311
so certainly not every
time I sit down to do work.

2542
01:34:45,311 --> 01:34:47,730
And I should also mention

2543
01:34:47,730 --> 01:34:49,650
that I still tend to do
the behavioral tools.

2544
01:34:49,650 --> 01:34:51,780
I'll tend to use five
minutes of binaural beats

2545
01:34:51,780 --> 01:34:53,682
or binaural beats
throughout the work session,

2546
01:34:53,682 --> 01:34:56,498
sometimes do a ice bath
or a cold shower before.

2547
01:34:56,498 --> 01:34:58,320
I don't want to give the impression

2548
01:34:58,320 --> 01:35:01,740
that I combine every tool
that I've talked about today

2549
01:35:01,740 --> 01:35:02,940
for a given workout.

2550
01:35:02,940 --> 01:35:05,850
I mean, that would be pretty
wild to take a cold shower,

2551
01:35:05,850 --> 01:35:08,190
pop an L-tyrosine, take an Alpha-GPC,

2552
01:35:08,190 --> 01:35:10,350
drink two espresso,
listen to binaural beats.

2553
01:35:10,350 --> 01:35:13,440
That to me seems like
a very inefficient way

2554
01:35:13,440 --> 01:35:14,334
to go about life.

2555
01:35:14,334 --> 01:35:18,930
In fact, I make it a
point to try and use tools

2556
01:35:18,930 --> 01:35:21,420
to increase my ability
to concentrate and focus,

2557
01:35:21,420 --> 01:35:24,060
but not to combine more
than two or three of them

2558
01:35:24,060 --> 01:35:24,893
at any one time.

2559
01:35:24,893 --> 01:35:25,800
And when I say two or three,

2560
01:35:25,800 --> 01:35:28,667
what I mean is I will use
supplements like Alpha-GPC,

2561
01:35:28,667 --> 01:35:31,800
L-Tyrosine and caffeine together
before certain work bouts,

2562
01:35:31,800 --> 01:35:33,720
I might use the visual practice

2563
01:35:33,720 --> 01:35:35,490
of focusing on a given
location for a minute

2564
01:35:35,490 --> 01:35:37,002
before I begin that work about,

2565
01:35:37,002 --> 01:35:38,940
I might combine those.

2566
01:35:38,940 --> 01:35:41,730
Then another time I
might take a cold shower

2567
01:35:41,730 --> 01:35:43,110
prior to doing some work.

2568
01:35:43,110 --> 01:35:45,810
Other days, I confess,
I've slept very well

2569
01:35:45,810 --> 01:35:49,530
or my enthusiasm about what
I'm about to work on is such

2570
01:35:49,530 --> 01:35:51,480
that I don't require any of these tools.

2571
01:35:51,480 --> 01:35:53,820
Again, there's no requirement,

2572
01:35:53,820 --> 01:35:55,800
there's no pressure to
use any of these tools,

2573
01:35:55,800 --> 01:35:58,375
behavioral, supplement based or otherwise.

2574
01:35:58,375 --> 01:36:02,010
It's simply a matter of using the tools

2575
01:36:02,010 --> 01:36:02,970
that are going to allow you

2576
01:36:02,970 --> 01:36:04,470
to achieve the states you want to achieve

2577
01:36:04,470 --> 01:36:07,860
and to improve your ability
to go into those states

2578
01:36:07,860 --> 01:36:09,210
without any help at all.

2579
01:36:09,210 --> 01:36:10,620
And this is what I find

2580
01:36:10,620 --> 01:36:12,540
particularly attractive about supplements.

2581
01:36:12,540 --> 01:36:14,070
It's not so much that they put you

2582
01:36:14,070 --> 01:36:16,290
into the ideal state for that work

2583
01:36:16,290 --> 01:36:18,150
and then you accomplish that work

2584
01:36:18,150 --> 01:36:20,044
and then you always rely
on those supplements.

2585
01:36:20,044 --> 01:36:22,260
I prefer to look at supplements

2586
01:36:22,260 --> 01:36:23,910
of the sort that I just described

2587
01:36:23,910 --> 01:36:27,561
as a route into a deeper trench
of focus and concentration

2588
01:36:27,561 --> 01:36:30,780
that I use as a tool to teach myself

2589
01:36:30,780 --> 01:36:32,400
to focus and concentrate more deeply,

2590
01:36:32,400 --> 01:36:34,470
such that I don't need those tools

2591
01:36:34,470 --> 01:36:37,403
every single time I try
and focus and concentrate.

2592
01:36:37,403 --> 01:36:39,390
I think this is an important point

2593
01:36:39,390 --> 01:36:41,850
because I think that many
people think of supplements

2594
01:36:41,850 --> 01:36:46,850
as a crutch or a way of
simply getting into a state

2595
01:36:46,877 --> 01:36:50,850
for which no other tool
will suffice or replace.

2596
01:36:50,850 --> 01:36:52,560
But in that context,

2597
01:36:52,560 --> 01:36:55,200
I want to remind you of the
larger context of pharmacology,

2598
01:36:55,200 --> 01:36:57,000
which is the vast landscape

2599
01:36:57,000 --> 01:36:59,580
of prescription pharmacology for ADHD,

2600
01:36:59,580 --> 01:37:01,860
for attention deficit
hyperactivity disorder.

2601
01:37:01,860 --> 01:37:05,370
Now I covered that
landscape in intense detail

2602
01:37:05,370 --> 01:37:07,754
on the episode on ADHD and focus.

2603
01:37:07,754 --> 01:37:11,450
And just to summarize, there is of course,

2604
01:37:11,450 --> 01:37:16,050
Adderall, Ritalin, Vyvanse,
Modafinil, Armodafinil,

2605
01:37:16,050 --> 01:37:17,031
a number of different compounds,

2606
01:37:17,031 --> 01:37:21,120
all of which generally
increase dopamine transmission

2607
01:37:21,120 --> 01:37:22,710
in the brain, so increasing dopamine,

2608
01:37:22,710 --> 01:37:25,260
and all of which generally
increase epinephrine,

2609
01:37:25,260 --> 01:37:27,544
adrenaline transmission
in the brain and body.

2610
01:37:27,544 --> 01:37:30,360
And many of those compounds

2611
01:37:30,360 --> 01:37:32,520
have been of tremendous benefit

2612
01:37:32,520 --> 01:37:35,490
to children and even some
adults who suffer from ADHD.

2613
01:37:35,490 --> 01:37:38,910
So properly prescribed at
the appropriate dosage,

2614
01:37:38,910 --> 01:37:41,910
those compounds can really help people

2615
01:37:41,910 --> 01:37:44,309
with clinically diagnosed ADHD.

2616
01:37:44,309 --> 01:37:48,270
The way they help those people
is a bit surprising, however.

2617
01:37:48,270 --> 01:37:50,820
You might think, well they
turn on the brain chemicals

2618
01:37:50,820 --> 01:37:53,080
that allow those people
to concentrate and focus.

2619
01:37:53,080 --> 01:37:54,245
That's true,

2620
01:37:54,245 --> 01:37:56,610
but they also have the benefit

2621
01:37:56,610 --> 01:38:00,510
of teaching those brain
circuits how to engage.

2622
01:38:00,510 --> 01:38:04,170
And that's one of the reasons
why somewhat paradoxically

2623
01:38:04,170 --> 01:38:07,470
giving a stimulant like
Ritalin or Adderall

2624
01:38:07,470 --> 01:38:09,960
to a kid that legitimately needs it,

2625
01:38:09,960 --> 01:38:12,690
obviously, you don't want to
do this without the oversight

2626
01:38:12,690 --> 01:38:15,810
and careful evaluation of a psychiatrist,

2627
01:38:15,810 --> 01:38:19,094
but giving that to a
kid who has severe ADHD,

2628
01:38:19,094 --> 01:38:22,230
you would think would make
them more rambunctious,

2629
01:38:22,230 --> 01:38:24,810
less able to focus and
more distractible overall.

2630
01:38:24,810 --> 01:38:28,137
After all, Ritalin,
Modafinil, Armodafinil,

2631
01:38:28,137 --> 01:38:29,490
all these things are stimulants.

2632
01:38:29,490 --> 01:38:30,420
So you take a kid

2633
01:38:30,420 --> 01:38:33,300
who has attention deficit
hyperactivity disorder

2634
01:38:33,300 --> 01:38:35,190
and give them these drugs

2635
01:38:35,190 --> 01:38:37,470
that increase transmission
of dopamine and epinephrine

2636
01:38:37,470 --> 01:38:38,760
and you think, wow,
it's going to make them

2637
01:38:38,760 --> 01:38:40,560
even more distractible and hyperactive

2638
01:38:40,560 --> 01:38:42,210
and indeed, it has the opposite effect.

2639
01:38:42,210 --> 01:38:44,055
It doesn't necessarily
make them feel calm,

2640
01:38:44,055 --> 01:38:47,460
but it makes them feel
that they can focus,

2641
01:38:47,460 --> 01:38:49,470
they really can anchor their attention.

2642
01:38:49,470 --> 01:38:52,231
And the idea is that it's
teaching those neural circuits

2643
01:38:52,231 --> 01:38:55,320
or those neural circuits
rather are teaching themselves

2644
01:38:55,320 --> 01:38:57,720
to engage and to focus and concentrate.

2645
01:38:57,720 --> 01:38:59,580
And the ideal situation is one in which

2646
01:38:59,580 --> 01:39:02,460
the total dosage of those
compounds, those drugs,

2647
01:39:02,460 --> 01:39:03,720
can be reduced over time

2648
01:39:03,720 --> 01:39:05,880
as those circuits learn to come online

2649
01:39:05,880 --> 01:39:07,230
through purely behavioral tools.

2650
01:39:07,230 --> 01:39:09,690
Now oftentimes, there's a
maintenance of those drugs

2651
01:39:09,690 --> 01:39:10,890
over long periods of time,

2652
01:39:10,890 --> 01:39:12,720
although there is a
common practice nowadays

2653
01:39:12,720 --> 01:39:15,029
of trying to diminish the dosage overall.

2654
01:39:15,029 --> 01:39:18,030
That's in the context of ADHD
and prescription medication

2655
01:39:18,030 --> 01:39:19,706
and I acknowledge that a lot,

2656
01:39:19,706 --> 01:39:24,706
indeed 80% or more of college
students say the statistics

2657
01:39:25,643 --> 01:39:28,440
are using prescription drugs

2658
01:39:28,440 --> 01:39:30,270
when they are not in fact

2659
01:39:30,270 --> 01:39:32,040
prescribed those prescription drugs.

2660
01:39:32,040 --> 01:39:33,570
So basically what I'm saying

2661
01:39:33,570 --> 01:39:35,100
is there are a lot of people using drugs

2662
01:39:35,100 --> 01:39:37,290
designed for ADHD and narcolepsy

2663
01:39:37,290 --> 01:39:38,763
because those drugs

2664
01:39:38,763 --> 01:39:41,940
will effectively increase
focus and concentration,

2665
01:39:41,940 --> 01:39:44,490
but I strongly discourage

2666
01:39:44,490 --> 01:39:46,980
the use of powerful prescription drugs

2667
01:39:46,980 --> 01:39:48,210
that have not been prescribed to you.

2668
01:39:48,210 --> 01:39:49,080
First of all, it's illegal.

2669
01:39:49,080 --> 01:39:50,820
Second of all, it's quite dangerous

2670
01:39:50,820 --> 01:39:53,790
to hit the accelerator
of those neural circuits

2671
01:39:53,790 --> 01:39:55,230
with such vigor

2672
01:39:55,230 --> 01:39:57,240
because it can increase dependency

2673
01:39:57,240 --> 01:39:58,860
and they can have a number
of other side effects

2674
01:39:58,860 --> 01:40:01,050
outside the context of
clinically diagnosed

2675
01:40:01,050 --> 01:40:04,385
and prescribed ADHD medication.

2676
01:40:04,385 --> 01:40:07,350
But in the context of supplementation,

2677
01:40:07,350 --> 01:40:12,350
the increase in dopamine,
acetylcholine and epinephrine

2678
01:40:12,450 --> 01:40:15,120
that one can achieve from say
500 milligrams of L-tyrosine,

2679
01:40:15,120 --> 01:40:20,120
300 milligrams of Alpha-GPC
and a cup of coffee

2680
01:40:20,190 --> 01:40:22,350
is going to be substantially less

2681
01:40:22,350 --> 01:40:24,060
than one would see for prescription drugs.

2682
01:40:24,060 --> 01:40:26,043
So you're getting a modest effect

2683
01:40:26,043 --> 01:40:29,880
that can similarly teach
those brain circuits

2684
01:40:29,880 --> 01:40:33,030
for focus and concentration
how to engage better.

2685
01:40:33,030 --> 01:40:35,820
But as a general backdrop to all of this,

2686
01:40:35,820 --> 01:40:38,400
I always say and I'll
say it again and again

2687
01:40:38,400 --> 01:40:39,930
probably until the day I die,

2688
01:40:39,930 --> 01:40:41,340
which hopefully is a long time from now,

2689
01:40:41,340 --> 01:40:43,950
but regardless, it'll be the same message,

2690
01:40:43,950 --> 01:40:46,923
I always believe that behavioral
tools should come first,

2691
01:40:46,923 --> 01:40:48,660
behavioral tools should come first.

2692
01:40:48,660 --> 01:40:50,250
Then focus on nutrition.

2693
01:40:50,250 --> 01:40:52,500
In fact, I would say
behavioral and nutrition tools,

2694
01:40:52,500 --> 01:40:54,635
and of course, get excellent sleep.

2695
01:40:54,635 --> 01:40:58,866
Then focus on supplementation and then,

2696
01:40:58,866 --> 01:41:01,830
and only if those are failing

2697
01:41:01,830 --> 01:41:03,450
to bring your brain and body

2698
01:41:03,450 --> 01:41:04,590
to the state you need to be in

2699
01:41:04,590 --> 01:41:07,419
to perform well in school
and work and life, et cetera

2700
01:41:07,419 --> 01:41:12,240
do I recommend that people
lean on prescription drugs.

2701
01:41:12,240 --> 01:41:13,290
Now there's a caveat to that,

2702
01:41:13,290 --> 01:41:16,521
which is in under conditions
like severe eating disorders,

2703
01:41:16,521 --> 01:41:20,105
obsessive compulsive
disorder, bipolar disorder,

2704
01:41:20,105 --> 01:41:25,105
depression where people are
truly at risk of suicide

2705
01:41:25,530 --> 01:41:27,480
or severe mental health effects

2706
01:41:27,480 --> 01:41:29,130
or behavioral health effects

2707
01:41:29,130 --> 01:41:31,920
and they're really at,
their lives are at risk

2708
01:41:31,920 --> 01:41:34,033
and their overall mood
and wellbeing is at risk,

2709
01:41:34,033 --> 01:41:37,050
it's often the case that
people cannot access

2710
01:41:37,050 --> 01:41:39,060
the brain states required

2711
01:41:39,060 --> 01:41:41,250
to shift themselves purely
with behavioral tools,

2712
01:41:41,250 --> 01:41:42,180
nutrition, et cetera.

2713
01:41:42,180 --> 01:41:44,910
So again, for the typical person

2714
01:41:44,910 --> 01:41:45,840
who's not suffering

2715
01:41:45,840 --> 01:41:47,521
from one of the psychiatric disorders

2716
01:41:47,521 --> 01:41:50,325
that I mentioned before or
other psychiatric disorders,

2717
01:41:50,325 --> 01:41:52,550
schizophrenia, et cetera,

2718
01:41:52,550 --> 01:41:56,760
I strongly encourage you to
look to behavioral tools first,

2719
01:41:56,760 --> 01:41:59,610
nutrition, then supplementation,

2720
01:41:59,610 --> 01:42:02,910
then and only if there's a remaining need,

2721
01:42:02,910 --> 01:42:04,358
to prescription drugs.

2722
01:42:04,358 --> 01:42:06,240
This contrasts very much

2723
01:42:06,240 --> 01:42:08,460
with the typical scenario
I hear about these days

2724
01:42:08,460 --> 01:42:10,890
where college students
or other people will say,

2725
01:42:10,890 --> 01:42:12,641
oh yeah, I hear that there's this drug,

2726
01:42:12,641 --> 01:42:15,797
Ritalin or Vyvanse that can
immediately put me into a state

2727
01:42:15,797 --> 01:42:17,880
of heightened focus and concentration.

2728
01:42:17,880 --> 01:42:19,680
Now listen, if you have ADHD,

2729
01:42:19,680 --> 01:42:21,840
by all means, talk to a physician,

2730
01:42:21,840 --> 01:42:23,430
talk to a great psychiatrist

2731
01:42:23,430 --> 01:42:25,290
and figure out whether or
not that's right for you.

2732
01:42:25,290 --> 01:42:26,520
But if you don't,

2733
01:42:26,520 --> 01:42:29,167
again, behavioral tools,
nutrition, supplementation,

2734
01:42:29,167 --> 01:42:32,910
and in particular, those behavioral tools

2735
01:42:32,910 --> 01:42:35,130
are going to be the ones
that are going to allow you

2736
01:42:35,130 --> 01:42:36,660
to teach your neural circuits

2737
01:42:36,660 --> 01:42:38,130
how to focus and concentrate better,

2738
01:42:38,130 --> 01:42:40,230
and I cannot overstate
the importance of that,

2739
01:42:40,230 --> 01:42:41,400
that the behavioral tools,

2740
01:42:41,400 --> 01:42:43,374
and to some extent the supplementation

2741
01:42:43,374 --> 01:42:45,360
combined with behavioral tools

2742
01:42:45,360 --> 01:42:48,630
really allow you to train
up your neural circuits

2743
01:42:48,630 --> 01:42:50,687
so that you can focus and concentrate

2744
01:42:50,687 --> 01:42:53,550
to the depth and the
degree and the duration

2745
01:42:53,550 --> 01:42:56,430
that's going to best serve
your mental and physical goals.

2746
01:42:56,430 --> 01:42:57,282
Now there's one other compound

2747
01:42:57,282 --> 01:43:00,418
that I've used from time to
time and that I continue to use

2748
01:43:00,418 --> 01:43:03,327
in order to increase
focus and concentration

2749
01:43:03,327 --> 01:43:06,120
and I will use this in combination

2750
01:43:06,120 --> 01:43:08,010
with the other supplements
I talked about before

2751
01:43:08,010 --> 01:43:09,780
and that's phenylethylamine.

2752
01:43:09,780 --> 01:43:12,780
Phenylethylamine is in the
dopamine synthesis pathway,

2753
01:43:12,780 --> 01:43:14,610
so it increases dopamine transmission

2754
01:43:14,610 --> 01:43:16,560
and tends to function a
little bit differently

2755
01:43:16,560 --> 01:43:17,442
than L-tyrosine.

2756
01:43:17,442 --> 01:43:20,850
So every once in a while,
I'll swap out L-tyrosine

2757
01:43:20,850 --> 01:43:23,850
and put in 500 milligrams
of phenylethylamine

2758
01:43:23,850 --> 01:43:27,210
or sometimes, if I really want
to push a little bit harder

2759
01:43:27,210 --> 01:43:28,356
on the dopamine system,

2760
01:43:28,356 --> 01:43:32,190
and I'm going to be doing a
long about of intense work,

2761
01:43:32,190 --> 01:43:34,827
I will take the 300
milligrams of Alpha-GPC,

2762
01:43:34,827 --> 01:43:37,350
the 500 milligrams of L-tyrosine,

2763
01:43:37,350 --> 01:43:39,236
I'll generally take
that with some caffeine,

2764
01:43:39,236 --> 01:43:40,770
and I should mention,

2765
01:43:40,770 --> 01:43:43,560
I don't go past about 100 or
200 milligrams of caffeine

2766
01:43:43,560 --> 01:43:45,360
'cause I don't really
like feeling too jittery,

2767
01:43:45,360 --> 01:43:46,290
that's not really my goal,

2768
01:43:46,290 --> 01:43:48,360
it's the goal to be alert,

2769
01:43:48,360 --> 01:43:51,360
but not so alert that I really
can't focus on anything,

2770
01:43:51,360 --> 01:43:54,480
I'm not interested in having
an anxiety attack after all,

2771
01:43:54,480 --> 01:43:56,790
but I'll sometimes either swap in

2772
01:43:56,790 --> 01:43:59,874
or I will add that 500
milligrams of phenylethylamine.

2773
01:43:59,874 --> 01:44:02,963
